WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.005
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.882 --> 00:15.885
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.585
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.716 --> 00:24.633
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.763 --> 00:27.984
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.115 --> 00:30.769
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:31.422 --> 00:33.816
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALRIGHT ♪

00:36.949 --> 00:38.821
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.951 --> 00:42.303
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.871 --> 00:49.353
♪ I'LL BE READY
[I'LL BE READY] ♪

00:49.484 --> 00:53.357
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR
[NO, DON'T YOU FEAR] ♪

00:53.488 --> 00:56.273
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.404 --> 00:59.885
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:00.016 --> 01:02.845
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.732 --> 01:22.821
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.952 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.480 --> 01:33.571
♪ I'LL BE READY
[I'LL BE READY] ♪

01:33.702 --> 01:37.401
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR
[NO, DON'T YOU FEAR] ♪

01:37.532 --> 01:40.709
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.839 --> 01:43.755
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.886 --> 01:47.019
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:01.686 --> 02:06.822
[GENTLE MUSIC]

03:41.351 --> 03:43.092
-I LOVE YOU, DIANA.

03:43.571 --> 03:45.964
I LOVE YOU MORE
THAN LIFE ITSELF.

03:46.704 --> 03:47.923
-OH, RUPERT, DON'T.

03:48.053 --> 03:49.490
-LEAVE HIM.

03:49.620 --> 03:51.622
LEAVE EVERYTHING.

03:52.275 --> 03:54.059
COME AWAY WITH ME.

03:54.190 --> 03:57.889
-I CAN'T, JONATHAN WON'T GRANT
ME A DIVORCE, YOU KNOW THAT.

03:58.629 --> 03:59.978
-DO YOU LOVE ME, DIANA?

04:00.109 --> 04:02.242
-RUPERT, WITH ALL MY HEART.

04:02.372 --> 04:05.375
-DO YOU LOVE ME MORE
THAN LIFE ITSELF?

04:07.116 --> 04:07.986
-YES.

04:08.117 --> 04:10.511
-THEN COME AWAY WITH ME NOW.

04:11.642 --> 04:12.774
-WHERE?

04:12.904 --> 04:16.255
-WHERE WE CAN BE
TOGETHER FOR ETERNITY.

04:17.257 --> 04:19.649
WHERE NOTHING CAN
EVER COME BETWEEN US.

04:21.261 --> 04:26.266
[JAZZ MUSIC]
[SPLASHING WAVES]

04:42.282 --> 04:46.198
TWO SOULS, ONE BREATH.

04:46.329 --> 04:51.291
[JAZZ MUSIC]

05:31.635 --> 05:32.723
-HEY, MORNING, DAD.

05:32.854 --> 05:33.855
-MORNING, PAL.

05:35.726 --> 05:38.076
-HEY, DAD, I DON'T GET IT,

05:38.729 --> 05:41.036
IF YOU'RE TAKING THE SCARAB
TO SAN DIEGO,

05:41.166 --> 05:43.212
THEN HOW COME WE HAVE TO DRIVE?

05:44.735 --> 05:46.737
-BECAUSE WE'RE MAKING
A STOP ALONG THE WAY.

05:47.347 --> 05:49.436
-WHERE?
-SOLANA BEACH.

05:49.566 --> 05:50.915
-WHAT'S IN SOLANA BEACH?

05:51.046 --> 05:53.614
-SIX FOOT SWELLS,
ACCORDING TO YOUR UNCLE.

05:53.744 --> 05:55.311
-MY UNCLE?

05:55.442 --> 05:56.617
UNCLE BUZZY?

05:56.747 --> 05:58.445
-YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT, AND KYLE.

05:58.575 --> 06:00.360
-WELL, WHAT ARE THEY
DOING IN SAN DIEGO?

06:00.490 --> 06:02.710
-THEY BOUGHT AN OLD SAILBOAT
AND THEY'RE LIVING ON BOARD

06:02.840 --> 06:03.754
WHILE THEY'RE RESTORING IT.

06:03.885 --> 06:05.539
-HOW COOL.

06:05.669 --> 06:07.279
CAN'T WAIT TO GO
SURFING WITH KYLE AGAIN.

06:07.410 --> 06:09.020
REMEMBER WHEN THEY
WERE HERE AND...

06:09.151 --> 06:11.806
-YEAH, HE ALMOST KILLED
HIMSELF SHOOTING THE PIER,

06:11.936 --> 06:13.373
BELIEVE ME, I REMEMBER.

06:14.330 --> 06:16.506
LOOK, I KNOW HE'S YOUR ONLY
COUSIN, BUT HE'S NOT EXACTLY

06:16.637 --> 06:19.509
WHAT I WOULD CALL
THE MOST POSITIVE ROLE MODEL.

06:20.815 --> 06:22.991
-KYLE: HEY, I'M GONNA
POP A CHILL, WANT ONE?

06:23.121 --> 06:24.209
-WHAT'S A CHILL?

06:24.340 --> 06:25.994
-A BEER.

06:26.124 --> 06:27.082
HOW OLD ARE YOU ANYWAY?

06:27.212 --> 06:29.345
-10 AND A HALF, ALMOST 11.

06:31.956 --> 06:33.044
-KNOCK YOURSELF OUT.

06:33.175 --> 06:34.742
-OH, NO, THANKS.

06:34.872 --> 06:36.483
-GO ON, TAKE A HIT,
IT'S NOT LIKE

06:36.613 --> 06:38.006
YOU'RE GONNA BE
DRIVING OR ANYTHING.

06:40.356 --> 06:41.879
[POP]
-OH!

06:44.186 --> 06:45.405
-MITCH: HEY, HOBIE!

06:49.496 --> 06:51.889
-WELL, DAD,
THAT WAS TWO YEARS AGO.

06:52.499 --> 06:54.152
PEOPLE CHANGE.

06:54.283 --> 06:57.373
WHO KNOWS, KYLE'S PROBABLY
LIKE THIS PERFECT KID NOW.

06:57.504 --> 07:00.550
-I DOUBT IT, NOT WITH
A FATHER LIKE BUZZ.

07:03.466 --> 07:05.468
HOW COME YOU NEVER
TOLD ME ABOUT KYLE?

07:07.209 --> 07:09.429
-I SUPPOSE 'CAUSE HIS MOTHER
NEVER TOLD ME ABOUT HIM.

07:10.386 --> 07:11.735
YOU REMEMBER
WHEN I WAS LIVING

07:11.866 --> 07:13.128
IN THAT COMMUNE UP IN BIG SUR?

07:14.172 --> 07:17.915
THERE WAS THIS LADY, FELICIA,
LOOKED LIKE JONI MITCHELL,

07:18.046 --> 07:19.830
I MEAN, SHE WAS BEAUTIFUL.

07:20.831 --> 07:24.444
ANYWAY, WE KINDA DUG EACH
OTHER, BUT, WELL, YOU KNOW ME,

07:24.574 --> 07:26.402
I'M NOT ONE TO STAY AROUND
ONE PLACE FOR TOO LONG.

07:27.490 --> 07:29.274
SHE NEVER TOLD ME SHE WAS
PREGNANT WHEN I SPLIT,

07:29.405 --> 07:30.711
I NEVER SAW HER AGAIN.

07:30.841 --> 07:32.452
-THEN HOW'D YOU
FIND OUT ABOUT KYLE?

07:33.322 --> 07:35.759
-SHE DIED ABOUT THREE MONTHS
AGO, THEY TRACKED ME DOWN

07:35.890 --> 07:37.413
IN BELLS BEACH IN AUSTRALIA.

07:38.022 --> 07:42.200
SO I CAME BACK,
PICKED HIM UP, HE'S MINE.

07:42.331 --> 07:46.030
-NO OFFENSE, BUT I MEAN,
ARE YOU SURE HE'S...

07:46.161 --> 07:47.554
-THAT HE'S MY KID?

07:47.684 --> 07:49.425
YOU WAIT TIL YOU SEE
HIM ON A BOARD, MAN.

07:50.600 --> 07:51.993
-UNBELIEVABLE.

07:52.994 --> 07:55.475
I MEAN, THAT'S WILD,
I MEAN, YOU'RE A FATHER.

07:55.605 --> 07:56.476
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

07:57.651 --> 07:58.869
-IT BEATS THE HELL OUT OF ME.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.610
-I'M SERIOUS.

08:00.741 --> 08:02.177
-I KNOW YOU'RE SERIOUS,
YOU'RE ALWAYS SERIOUS.

08:02.307 --> 08:03.570
YOU WERE BORN SERIOUS.

08:03.700 --> 08:04.658
I'M THE ONLY SCREW-UP
IN THIS FAMILY.

08:04.788 --> 08:06.660
I DON'T KNOW, I DON'T KNOW.

08:27.071 --> 08:27.942
-GOOD JOB.

08:28.856 --> 08:31.511
-YEAH. ALL RIGHT.
WHOO!

08:50.878 --> 08:51.705
-HI.

08:51.835 --> 08:53.533
-WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?

08:54.534 --> 08:56.361
-SHE'S JUST AN OLD
FRIEND FROM MALIBU HIGH.

08:57.493 --> 08:58.538
-I DON'T REMEMBER HER.

08:59.408 --> 09:01.715
-SHE MUST HAVE LEFT
BEFORE YOU GOT THERE.

09:02.803 --> 09:04.587
-ALL THESE GIRLS
FROM YOUR PAST, MATT,

09:04.718 --> 09:06.633
IT'S FUNNY HOW THEY
JUST KEEP POPPING UP.

09:06.763 --> 09:07.547
-SUMMER...

09:07.677 --> 09:09.200
-YOU GUYS ALL SET?

09:09.331 --> 09:11.638
-YEAH, WHAT'S THE
BEST TIME SO FAR?

09:11.768 --> 09:14.858
-MITCH AND C.J.,
ONE MINUTE AND 47 SECONDS.

09:15.598 --> 09:17.295
THEY'VE ALREADY QUALIFIED.

09:17.426 --> 09:19.471
-QUALIFIED? I THOUGHT THIS
WAS JUST A TRAINING SESSION.

09:19.602 --> 09:21.735
-IT IS, BUT THERE'S
A SPECIAL BONUS

09:21.865 --> 09:23.258
FOR THE TWO FASTEST TIMES.

09:24.564 --> 09:26.609
A TEAM FROM BAYWATCH HAS
BEEN INVITED TO SAN DIEGO

09:26.740 --> 09:28.611
TO DEMONSTRATE WATER-BASED
RESCUE OPERATIONS.

09:30.134 --> 09:32.789
SO FAR, IT'S MITCH,
C.J., AND MYSELF.

09:33.573 --> 09:35.313
COME IN UNDER TWO MINUTES
AND YOU'VE GOT

09:35.444 --> 09:37.925
A FREE WEEKEND
AT THE HOTEL DEL CORONADO.

09:39.361 --> 09:40.362
-ALRIGHT, LET'S DO IT.

09:40.492 --> 09:41.798
SEE YOU LATER.

09:41.929 --> 09:43.365
-GOOD LUCK.

09:54.550 --> 09:55.682
GET READY!

09:58.249 --> 09:59.120
GO!

10:00.556 --> 10:02.645
[ENGINE ROARING]

10:02.776 --> 10:07.650
[ROCK MUSIC]

11:24.727 --> 11:26.468
ONE MINUTE, 57 SECONDS.

11:27.121 --> 11:28.122
YOU'RE IN!

11:28.252 --> 11:29.471
-YEAH!

11:30.733 --> 11:32.517
DEL CORONADO, HERE WE COME!

11:32.648 --> 11:33.823
[GENTLE MUSIC]

11:51.188 --> 11:51.972
-STEPHANIE: HELLO.

11:52.102 --> 11:53.277
-MATT: HEY.

11:53.408 --> 11:54.931
STEPHANIE: HI,
HOW WAS YOUR DRIVE?

11:55.062 --> 11:56.803
-MATT: EXCELLENT, WE CAME
DOWN THE COAST HIGHWAY.

11:56.933 --> 11:58.587
-STEPHANIE: OURS WAS GREAT.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.330
-C.J.: GUYS,
THIS PLACE IS FANTASTIC.

12:02.460 --> 12:04.332
-SUMMER: YEAH,
I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE THE ROOMS.

12:05.115 --> 12:06.334
-HEY.

12:06.464 --> 12:07.639
-HI, YOU GUYS,
THIS IS MEL DAWSON

12:07.770 --> 12:09.119
OF THE CORONADO
ISLAND LIFEGUARDS.

12:09.250 --> 12:09.990
-HOW YOU DOING?
-HI, I'M SUMMER.

12:10.120 --> 12:10.991
-MATT.

12:11.121 --> 12:12.079
-NICE TO MEET YOU, HI.

12:12.209 --> 12:13.994
HOW YOU DOING.
-C.J.

12:14.124 --> 12:15.822
-THANKS FOR COMING, I DON'T
KNOW WHAT STEPHANIE TOLD YOU,

12:15.952 --> 12:17.388
BUT WE'VE BEEN TRYING TO ADD

12:17.519 --> 12:18.999
A WATER-BASED UNIT
AROUND HERE FOR YEARS.

12:19.129 --> 12:21.175
I FINALLY FIGURED THE ONLY
WAY TO GET THE FUNDING FROM

12:21.305 --> 12:23.830
THE CITY COUNCIL IS TO SHOW
THEM WHAT THEY'D BE MISSING.

12:23.960 --> 12:25.135
ANYWAY, I UNDERSTAND
YOU GUYS HAVE HAD

12:25.266 --> 12:26.963
SOME SUCCESS WITH YOUR SCARABS,

12:27.094 --> 12:29.836
SO I CALLED UP LIEUTENANT HOLDEN
AND I BEGGED HER FOR HELP.

12:31.489 --> 12:34.449
-SUMMER, ARE YOU WITH US?

12:34.579 --> 12:36.103
-OH, YEAH, I'M SORRY.

12:36.233 --> 12:37.931
-IT'S OKAY, I SCHEDULED
THE FORMAL BRIEFING FOR

12:38.061 --> 12:40.847
LATER ON TONIGHT, SO YOU'LL
HAVE SOME FREE TIME UNTIL THEN.

12:40.977 --> 12:43.893
BUT FEEL FREE TO CALL ME
IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS.

12:48.332 --> 12:52.380
[GENTLE MUSIC]

13:08.265 --> 13:09.136
-THERE THEY ARE.

13:14.924 --> 13:17.971
-DAD, DO YOU EVER WISH
YOU AND BUZZY WERE CLOSER?

13:18.972 --> 13:21.365
WELL, YOU GUYS WERE REALLY TIGHT
WHEN YOU WERE YOUNG, RIGHT?

13:21.496 --> 13:25.630
-YEAH, WE WERE, BUT WHEN
BUZZY LEFT HOME AT 17,

13:26.370 --> 13:29.199
I GUESS OUR LIVES JUST WENT
OFF IN DIFFERENT DIRECTIONS.

13:29.330 --> 13:32.072
-YOU MEAN YOU SETTLED
DOWN AND BUZZY'S STILL

13:32.202 --> 13:34.161
OUT THERE SEARCHING
FOR THE PERFECT WAVE?

13:34.291 --> 13:35.771
-SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

13:37.294 --> 13:41.037
-HEY! HEY, THEY'RE
HERE, COME ON!

13:42.560 --> 13:45.172
HEY, COME ON DOWN HERE,
YOU WUSSES.

13:45.302 --> 13:46.477
COME ON!

13:56.313 --> 13:58.533
HEY, BRO!
-HEY!

14:00.056 --> 14:00.840
HOW YOU DOING?

14:00.970 --> 14:02.058
-MAN, I MISSED YOU.

14:02.189 --> 14:04.365
-YOU LOOK GREAT.
-I MISSED YOU.

14:04.495 --> 14:06.106
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
YOU SEE ME OUT THERE,
NOT BAD FOR AN OLD HAS-BEEN.

14:06.236 --> 14:08.630
-TOOK THE WORDS RIGHT
OUT OF MY MOUTH, OLD HAS-BEEN.

14:08.760 --> 14:10.327
KYLE, HEY, COME HERE, PAL!

14:10.458 --> 14:13.765
OH, MAN.
LOOK AT YOU, YOU GOT BIG!

14:13.896 --> 14:15.593
-HEY, CAN YOU SHOW
ME THAT CUT BACK MOVE?

14:15.724 --> 14:17.595
-YEAH, OF COURSE, GO ON OUT,
I'LL BE RIGHT OUT THERE.

14:17.726 --> 14:19.467
-GREAT, SEE YA.
-ALRIGHT.

14:19.597 --> 14:20.903
COME ON, KYLE, LET'S GO!

14:21.034 --> 14:22.078
-GO ON OUT.

14:27.518 --> 14:30.173
-HEY, MITCH, MITCH,
YOU REMEMBER

14:30.304 --> 14:32.262
THAT CUT BACK MOVE
I TAUGHT YOU, MAN?

14:33.307 --> 14:36.963
-GEEZ, BUZZ, I DON'T KNOW,
YOU TAUGHT ME SO MUCH.

14:37.615 --> 14:39.008
-YOU BETTER BELIEVE IT, BRO.

14:40.531 --> 14:42.707
WHY DON'T YOU GET YOUR BOARD?
WE'LL SEE HOW MUCH YOU REMEMBER.

14:42.838 --> 14:44.231
-PIECE OF CAKE.

14:45.580 --> 14:50.585
[GENTLE MUSIC]

15:01.204 --> 15:04.947
[WIND BLOWING]
[EERIE MUSIC]

15:20.397 --> 15:24.314
[WIND BLOWING]
[EERIE MUSIC]

15:44.421 --> 15:46.510
[PHONE RINGING]

15:50.471 --> 15:51.515
-HELLO?

15:52.690 --> 15:53.648
[WIND BLOWING]

15:53.778 --> 15:54.910
HELLO?

15:55.041 --> 15:56.390
[DOOR SLAMMING]

15:57.043 --> 16:01.656
[EERIE MUSIC]

16:13.146 --> 16:14.625
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

16:15.583 --> 16:17.237
SOMEBODY OPEN THE DOOR!

16:17.367 --> 16:18.542
HELP ME!

16:18.673 --> 16:19.935
-MATT: SUMMER?

16:20.066 --> 16:22.198
-MATT? MATT,
I CAN'T OPEN THE DOOR.

16:24.809 --> 16:25.680
-GIVE ME THE KEY.

16:25.810 --> 16:26.724
-HOW?

16:26.855 --> 16:28.117
-SLIDE IT UNDER THE DOOR.

16:38.040 --> 16:39.694
THE LOCK MUST HAVE JAMMED.

16:39.824 --> 16:42.001
YOU SHOULD CALL THE FRONT DESK
AND HAVE IT FIXED.

16:46.657 --> 16:48.007
[LAUGHING]

16:49.573 --> 16:51.575
DOES THIS MEAN YOU'RE
NOT MAD AT ME ANYMORE?

16:55.014 --> 16:57.320
OKAY, WHAT IF I PROMISE TO NEVER

16:57.451 --> 17:00.367
EVEN SO MUCH AS LOOK
AT ANOTHER GIRL?

17:01.237 --> 17:02.369
EVER AGAIN.

17:03.152 --> 17:04.458
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

17:05.285 --> 17:07.416
-WELL, THEN YOU WOULD LOSE
YOUR JOB BECAUSE YOU CAN'T

17:07.548 --> 17:09.854
BE A LIFEGUARD AND NOT
LOOK AT BEAUTIFUL WOMEN.

17:09.984 --> 17:13.075
-OKAY, THEN I'LL LOOK
AT THE BEAUTIFUL WOMEN,

17:13.205 --> 17:14.424
BUT I'LL THINK OF YOU.

17:19.646 --> 17:21.518
WHAT'S WRONG?
-I DON'T KNOW.

17:21.648 --> 17:22.867
-WHY'D YOU STOP?

17:23.564 --> 17:26.958
-I JUST FEEL LIKE SOMEBODY
IS WATCHING US OR SOMETHING.

17:27.611 --> 17:28.786
-WATCHING US?

17:28.917 --> 17:30.266
COME ON, SUMMER,
YOU CAN COME UP WITH

17:30.397 --> 17:31.615
A BETTER EXCUSE THAN THAT.

17:31.746 --> 17:33.748
-NO, IT'S NOT AN EXCUSE, MATT,

17:34.444 --> 17:37.143
SOMETHING REALLY WEIRD
IS GOING ON IN THIS ROOM.

17:38.840 --> 17:40.668
COME ON,
LET'S JUST GO FOR A SWIM.

17:40.798 --> 17:42.626
-WE'VE GOT ALL DAY TO SWIM.

17:46.543 --> 17:48.023
[CRASH]

17:54.769 --> 17:58.294
[ROCK MUSIC]

18:10.698 --> 18:13.657
♪ WE ALL, WE ALL

18:13.788 --> 18:17.400
♪ HAVE A LITTLE TIME TO WASTE

18:18.749 --> 18:21.404
♪ YOU ARE YOU ARE

18:21.535 --> 18:24.146
♪ A PICTURE PERFECT DREAM

18:24.277 --> 18:25.800
♪ OF FATE

18:26.975 --> 18:30.239
♪ AND EVERY NOW AND THEN I FEEL I FALL

18:30.761 --> 18:35.070
♪ I FALL IN YOUR EYES
♪ I FALL INTO PARADISE ♪

18:35.201 --> 18:38.117
♪ EVERY NOW AND THEN I HEAR A CALL

18:38.682 --> 18:39.944
♪ A CALL IN THE NIGHT ♪

18:40.467 --> 18:43.339
♪ A CALL FROM AN ANGELS VOICE ♪

18:43.470 --> 18:46.734
♪ COME ON BABY OPEN UP YOUR EYES

18:51.391 --> 18:54.698
♪ COME ON BABY DON'T YOU REALIZE

18:58.572 --> 19:01.531
♪ WE ALL, WE ALL

19:01.662 --> 19:03.620
♪ HAVE A LITTLE TIME

19:04.230 --> 19:07.581
♪ TO WASTE, YOU ARE ♪

19:08.234 --> 19:11.802
♪ YOU ARE A PICTURE PERFECT DREAM ♪

19:11.933 --> 19:13.282
♪ OF FATE

19:15.197 --> 19:18.331
♪ AND EVERY NOW AND THEN I FEEL I FALL

19:18.940 --> 19:20.637
♪ I FALL IN YOUR EYES ♪

19:20.768 --> 19:23.074
♪ I FALL INTO PARADISE

19:23.205 --> 19:26.556
♪ EVERY NOW AND THEN I HEAR A CALL

19:26.687 --> 19:28.558
♪ A CALL IN THE NIGHT

19:28.689 --> 19:31.082
♪ A CALL FROM AN ANGELS VOICE

19:31.213 --> 19:34.782
♪ COME ON BABY OPEN UP YOUR EYES

19:39.439 --> 19:42.746
♪ COME ON BABY DON'T YOU REALIZE

19:47.011 --> 19:48.361
-HEY, WHAT'S THIS? WHAT'S THIS?

19:48.491 --> 19:50.363
WHAT'S THIS? WHAT'S THIS?

19:52.016 --> 19:53.801
-YOU LOOK SO LONELY.

19:54.671 --> 19:56.238
HOW COME YOU'RE HERE
ALL BY YOURSELF?

20:01.765 --> 20:03.114
-HIS NAME'S ROCKY.

20:05.726 --> 20:06.944
-HI, ROCKY.

20:07.075 --> 20:08.424
-WHAT'S YOURS?

20:09.164 --> 20:11.732
-C.J.
-HI, C.J., KEITH TRAVIS.

20:11.862 --> 20:14.125
-I KNOW, I SAW
THE SHOW THREE TIMES.

20:15.953 --> 20:17.825
-YOU WANNA FEED HIM?
-OH, COULD I?

20:17.955 --> 20:19.305
-SURE, JUST WATCH
HOW I DO THIS.

20:19.435 --> 20:20.915
TAKE HIM BY THE TAIL.
-OKAY.

20:21.045 --> 20:23.961
-SHE'S SO...
YOU'RE READY.

20:24.092 --> 20:25.702
JUST LAY IT RIGHT THERE
IN HER MOUTH.

20:26.877 --> 20:29.837
OH, YES, SEE THAT?

20:29.967 --> 20:32.056
-OKAY, ROCKY, OPEN UP.

20:32.187 --> 20:34.320
HOW COME HE'S SO ISOLATED
FROM THE REST OF THE GROUP?

20:34.450 --> 20:38.846
-WELL, HIS MOTHER
DIED DURING CHILDBIRTH.

20:38.976 --> 20:40.891
WE RESCUED HIM
AND BROUGHT HIM HERE,

20:41.022 --> 20:43.677
FED HIM, GOT HIM HEALTHY,
UNFORTUNATELY,

20:43.807 --> 20:45.766
NONE OF THE OTHER FEMALES
WANT TO BOND WITH HIM.

20:46.375 --> 20:48.856
-OH, THAT'S SO SAD.

20:48.986 --> 20:50.379
ALL HE WANTS IS A MOMMY.

20:52.251 --> 20:54.688
-WELL, I THINK RIGHT NOW HE'D
SETTLE FOR A FEW MORE FISH.

20:55.254 --> 20:57.256
[LAUGHTER]

20:58.779 --> 21:00.302
[SQUEAKS]
-HI.

21:12.619 --> 21:14.098
-WHAT DID THEY SAY?

21:14.621 --> 21:16.013
DID YOU GET A ROOM?

21:16.144 --> 21:18.581
-NO, THE HOTEL WAS
TOTALLY BOOKED SOLID.

21:20.975 --> 21:22.977
-WELL, YOU COULD
ALWAYS STAY IN MY ROOM.

21:26.067 --> 21:27.373
SUMMER, LOOK,

21:29.810 --> 21:30.898
WHY DON'T YOU RELAX?

21:31.855 --> 21:34.075
WE'RE AT ONE OF THE MOST
ROMANTIC HOTELS IN THE WORLD,

21:35.424 --> 21:36.904
LET'S NOT LET IT GO TO WASTE.

21:38.079 --> 21:39.123
OKAY?

21:47.436 --> 21:48.698
HEY!

21:58.621 --> 22:01.232
-THEY'RE REALLY GETTING ALONG
GREAT, MAN, THAT'S NICE.

22:02.495 --> 22:03.974
KYLE DOESN'T HAVE
A LOT OF FRIENDS.

22:04.932 --> 22:06.325
-WHAT DO YOU EXPECT?

22:06.455 --> 22:07.717
YOU NEVER STAY
IN ONE PLACE LONG ENOUGH

22:07.848 --> 22:09.458
FOR HIM TO MAKE ANY.

22:09.589 --> 22:11.373
-WATCH IT, MAN,
YOU'RE STARTING
TO SOUND LIKE DAD.

22:12.983 --> 22:14.507
-IF YOU'RE GONNA BE
LIVING DOWN HERE NOW,

22:14.637 --> 22:15.682
MAYBE WE CAN GET THE KIDS
TOGETHER MORE OFTEN.

22:17.118 --> 22:18.641
-THAT'S WHAT I WAS HOPING.

22:18.772 --> 22:20.339
-WHAT ARE YOUR PLANS ANYWAY?

22:20.469 --> 22:21.862
YOU GONNA STAY IN SAN DIEGO?

22:25.082 --> 22:26.040
-DOESN'T REALLY LOOK THAT WAY.

22:26.780 --> 22:27.563
-WHY NOT?

22:29.348 --> 22:31.480
-'CAUSE THIS
RELATIONSHIP DIDN'T REALLY

22:31.611 --> 22:33.003
COME TOGETHER THE WAY
I EXPECTED IT TO.

22:33.134 --> 22:34.701
I MEAN, KYLE'S A GREAT
KID AND ALL THAT,

22:34.831 --> 22:38.269
BUT ME AS A FATHER,
I'M REALLY NOT CUT OUT FOR THAT.

22:38.400 --> 22:40.663
I CAN HARDLY TAKE
CARE OF MYSELF.

22:40.794 --> 22:42.099
YOU KNOW THAT, YOU KNOW ME.

22:43.797 --> 22:44.928
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

22:45.059 --> 22:47.583
-LOOK, WHEN I FINISH
WORK ON THE BOAT,

22:47.714 --> 22:49.803
I'M GONNA SAIL TO
NEW ZEALAND, SOLO.

22:51.326 --> 22:52.240
-SOLO?

22:54.982 --> 22:56.853
WHAT ABOUT YOUR SON, BUZZ?

22:59.334 --> 23:00.596
-I WAS KINDA HOPING
HE COULD LIVE WITH YOU.

23:00.727 --> 23:02.119
-WHAT ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

23:04.470 --> 23:06.428
YOU ACTUALLY EXPECTED ME
TO SAY YES, DIDN'T YOU?

23:07.603 --> 23:09.910
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA
GROW UP ANYWAY?

23:10.040 --> 23:11.825
YOU'VE BEEN RUNNING
AWAY FROM HOME

23:11.955 --> 23:13.957
SINCE YOU WERE 17 YEARS OLD,
IT'S TIME TO CALL IT A CAREER.

23:14.088 --> 23:16.873
BUZZ, YOU'RE A FATHER NOW,
KYLE IS YOUR RESPONSIBILITY.

23:17.004 --> 23:18.397
-LOOK, MITCH, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO TAKE HIM, ALRIGHT?

23:18.527 --> 23:20.137
I'VE MADE A DECISION TO SPLIT,

23:20.268 --> 23:22.531
IF YOU DON'T WANT HIM,
HE GOES TO THE FOSTER HOME.

23:26.666 --> 23:28.232
-HEY, DAD, IS DINNER READY YET?

23:29.146 --> 23:30.713
-COUPLE OF MINUTES,
WE'LL CALL YA.

23:30.844 --> 23:32.193
-ALRIGHT.

23:35.979 --> 23:37.416
-YOU'RE UNBELIEVABLE.

23:42.725 --> 23:47.164
[EERIE MUSIC]

23:56.043 --> 23:58.175
-MM, DON'T STOP.

24:01.135 --> 24:02.092
-DON'T STOP WHAT?

24:03.267 --> 24:04.355
-KISSING ME.

24:06.967 --> 24:07.968
-KISSING YOU?

24:10.927 --> 24:12.494
-YOU WEREN'T JUST KISSING ME?

24:13.321 --> 24:14.278
-NO.

24:15.062 --> 24:16.324
-MATT.

24:18.108 --> 24:19.370
-YOU MUST HAVE BEEN DREAMING.

24:21.416 --> 24:25.681
[EERIE MUSIC]

24:41.567 --> 24:42.829
-SOME HOTEL, HUH?

24:44.918 --> 24:46.702
I CAME HERE TO STUDY
ARCHITECTURE WHEN
I WAS IN COLLEGE.

24:46.833 --> 24:49.226
THIS IS THE LARGEST WOOD
STRUCTURE ON THE WEST COAST.

24:50.532 --> 24:51.533
IF YOU CARE.

24:52.578 --> 24:54.884
ALRIGHT, PAL, WHAT'S UP?

24:55.015 --> 24:56.103
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

24:58.061 --> 25:00.847
-DAD, IS UNCLE BUZZY
REALLY THINKING ABOUT

25:00.977 --> 25:02.370
PUTTING KYLE IN A FOSTER HOME?

25:03.763 --> 25:04.764
-DID KYLE TELL YOU THAT?

25:06.635 --> 25:08.507
-IS IT TRUE?

25:08.637 --> 25:10.770
-WELL, UNCLE BUZZY IS THINKING
ABOUT SAILING TO NEW ZEALAND.

25:10.900 --> 25:12.815
I THINK THAT'S ONE
OF HIS OPTIONS, YEAH.

25:12.946 --> 25:14.774
-WHY CAN'T KYLE
COME LIVE WITH US?

25:15.383 --> 25:16.993
-BECAUSE YOU DON'T JUST
PASS YOUR KID AROUND

25:17.124 --> 25:18.908
EVERY TIME YOU NEED SPACE.

25:19.039 --> 25:20.910
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE IT
IF I DUMPED YOU ON BUZZY WHILE

25:21.041 --> 25:23.391
I WENT OVER TO SWITZERLAND
TO GO SKIING FOR THE WINTER?

25:24.000 --> 25:26.916
HOBIE, FAMILIES
DON'T WORK THAT WAY.

25:28.265 --> 25:31.355
LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE
CLOSE TO KYLE.

25:31.486 --> 25:33.706
-YOU HAD A BROTHER WHEN
YOU WERE GROWING UP,

25:33.836 --> 25:36.752
I'M ALL BY MYSELF,
I GET LONELY SOMETIMES.

25:37.492 --> 25:38.537
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

25:38.667 --> 25:40.669
-YEAH, YEAH, I DO.

25:41.757 --> 25:43.803
-BESIDES, I THINK
IT'D BE GOOD FOR KYLE

25:43.933 --> 25:45.326
TO COME LIVE WITH US,

25:45.456 --> 25:47.589
STAY IN A REAL HOUSE
WITH A REAL FAMILY.

25:48.198 --> 25:49.591
HE'S NEVER EVEN GONE
TO THE SAME SCHOOL

25:49.722 --> 25:51.898
FOR TWO SEMESTERS IN A ROW.

25:52.028 --> 25:54.596
I KNOW THIS ISN'T AN EASY
DECISION FOR YOU TO MAKE,

25:55.858 --> 25:57.294
BUT JUST THINK ABOUT IT, OKAY?

25:57.425 --> 26:00.167
-OKAY, I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

26:00.297 --> 26:01.690
-THANKS.

26:08.218 --> 26:11.700
-SO, C.J., WHERE'D YOU
RUSH OFF TO THIS AFTERNOON?

26:12.222 --> 26:13.572
DID YOU GO SHOPPING IN TIJUANA?

26:13.702 --> 26:17.053
-NO, I WENT TO SEA WORLD.

26:17.184 --> 26:18.881
-SEA WORLD?

26:19.012 --> 26:21.928
-YEAH, I GO TO SEA WORLD
EVERY TIME I'M IN SAN DIEGO.

26:22.058 --> 26:23.538
-WELL, DID YOU HAVE A GOOD TIME?

26:23.669 --> 26:26.019
-WELL, I GOT TO
FEED A BABY DOLPHIN,

26:27.107 --> 26:30.371
AND I MET A GREAT GUY.

26:32.155 --> 26:34.505
SO, I GUESS YOU COULD
SAY IT WAS PRETTY GOOD.

26:35.985 --> 26:37.030
-I WANNA HEAR ABOUT THIS.

26:37.160 --> 26:38.422
-DOLPHIN OR THE GUY?

26:38.553 --> 26:40.816
-[LAUGHING]
LET'S START WITH THE GUY.

26:42.122 --> 26:45.386
-OKAY, HE WORKS AT SEA WORLD
WITH THE MARINE MAMMAL

26:45.516 --> 26:49.172
RESCUE PROGRAM, AND HE
ALSO PERFORMS IN THE SHOWS.

26:49.303 --> 26:54.525
HE'S SMART, HE'S TALENTED,
HE'S GORGEOUS,

26:55.614 --> 27:01.489
AND HE TAKES CARE OF LITTLE,
POOR, BABY, STRANDED ANIMALS.

27:03.796 --> 27:04.797
I THINK I'M IN LOVE.

27:04.927 --> 27:07.016
-[SIGHS] HERE WE GO AGAIN.

27:07.147 --> 27:09.453
C.J., PLEASE,
YOU CAN'T FALL IN LOVE

27:09.584 --> 27:11.064
WITH EVERY MAN YOU MEET.

27:11.717 --> 27:13.370
-HOW ABOUT A GUY
YOU'VE NEVER MET?

27:14.241 --> 27:15.111
-HUH?

27:17.374 --> 27:19.159
-LIKE MAYBE HE
DOESN'T EVEN EXIST,

27:19.289 --> 27:21.248
BUT YOU CAN JUST
FEEL HIS PRESENCE.

27:24.077 --> 27:25.556
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

27:25.687 --> 27:27.863
-SOMETHING REALLY
STRANGE HAS BEEN GOING ON

27:27.994 --> 27:30.736
EVER SINCE WE GOT TO
THIS HOTEL, EITHER THAT

27:30.866 --> 27:32.825
OR I'M, LIKE, TOTALLY
HALLUCINATING.

27:32.955 --> 27:34.827
-SUMMER, ARE YOU ALRIGHT?

27:34.957 --> 27:36.959
-I DON'T KNOW.

27:37.090 --> 27:39.005
IT'S JUST THAT EVER
SINCE WE GOT HERE,

27:39.135 --> 27:41.398
I'VE FELT LIKE SOMEBODY'S
BEEN WATCHING ME,

27:42.312 --> 27:45.228
OUTSIDE, EVEN IN MY HOTEL ROOM.

27:45.968 --> 27:47.491
AND THEN, TODAY,
WHEN I WAS SUNBATHING,

27:47.622 --> 27:49.145
HE JUST STARTED KISSING ME.

27:49.276 --> 27:50.712
-WHO STARTED KISSING YOU?

27:50.843 --> 27:52.583
-I DON'T KNOW.

27:52.714 --> 27:56.022
I MEAN, THERE WAS NOBODY
THERE, EXCEPT MATT,

27:56.152 --> 27:57.501
AND HE SAID HE DIDN'T DO IT.

27:58.851 --> 28:02.593
BESIDES, MATT HAS NEVER
KISSED ME LIKE THAT BEFORE.

28:03.594 --> 28:05.858
IT WAS THE MOST
PASSIONATE, TENDER KISS

28:05.988 --> 28:08.774
I HAVE EVER FELT
IN MY WHOLE LIFE.

28:23.179 --> 28:24.703
[PHONE RINGING]

28:26.226 --> 28:27.009
HELLO?

28:27.140 --> 28:28.489
-HI.

28:28.619 --> 28:30.186
HOW YOU DOING?

28:30.317 --> 28:31.753
-I'M OKAY.

28:31.884 --> 28:33.015
-WELL, YOU SURE YOU
DON'T WANT ANY COMPANY?

28:33.146 --> 28:35.278
-NO, MATT, I'M REALLY EXHAUSTED.

28:35.409 --> 28:36.845
I'M JUST GONNA GO
TO SLEEP, OKAY?

28:37.846 --> 28:38.760
-WELL, SWEET DREAMS.

28:39.456 --> 28:40.588
-GOODNIGHT.

28:51.033 --> 28:55.734
[EERIE MUSIC]

28:55.864 --> 29:01.087
[WIND BLOWING]

29:05.395 --> 29:09.835
[HEAVY BREATHING]

29:29.680 --> 29:30.899
-MAN: HELP US!

29:33.902 --> 29:35.034
-WOMAN: OVER HERE.

29:43.085 --> 29:46.828
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]
[ENGINES ROARING]

29:53.487 --> 29:56.359
LIFEGUARD

29:59.885 --> 30:04.454
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

30:05.978 --> 30:08.284
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

30:10.678 --> 30:13.594
[SHOUTING]

30:13.724 --> 30:16.205
SCARAB
BAYWATCH

31:18.354 --> 31:20.443
-MAN: HERE THEY COME.
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY.

31:34.283 --> 31:35.981
-HELP! HELP!

31:36.111 --> 31:38.679
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

31:49.908 --> 31:51.779
[SHOUTING]

31:51.910 --> 31:55.826
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

32:08.535 --> 32:10.102
-STEPHANIE: OKAY.

32:31.993 --> 32:33.168
-MAN: THANKS.

32:58.628 --> 33:00.674
-WOMAN: HELP!
I'M IN HERE!

33:01.631 --> 33:04.895
-MOVE AWAY FROM THE DOOR.
-OKAY.

33:05.766 --> 33:06.985
-COME ON.

33:09.813 --> 33:11.554
-WOMAN: I'M GLAD
YOU GUYS ARE HERE.

33:36.362 --> 33:38.190
-THAT'S IT, CAPTAIN,
ANY QUESTIONS?

33:39.104 --> 33:41.193
-NO, I THINK THEY
GET THE PICTURE.

33:41.323 --> 33:43.543
THANKS, STEPH.
-ANYTIME.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.852
-LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
I'M NOT SURE I CAN ADD ANYTHING

33:48.983 --> 33:50.115
TO WHAT YOU'VE JUST SEEN.

33:51.029 --> 33:52.856
EXCEPT FOR,
GIVEN OUR DEPARTMENT'S
CURRENT CAPABILITIES,

33:52.987 --> 33:55.207
WE COULD NOT HAVE RESPONDED
TO THAT TYPE OF AN EMERGENCY

33:55.337 --> 33:56.730
IN A SIMILAR FASHION.

33:57.339 --> 33:58.906
THE UNDENIABLE FACT IS,

33:59.037 --> 34:02.127
THE SCARAB AND THE WAVERUNNERS
WILL SAVE LIVES.

34:08.089 --> 34:09.786
-HEY, YOU GUYS
READY TO SHOVE OFF?

34:09.917 --> 34:11.136
-NOT EXACTLY.

34:11.875 --> 34:12.789
WE'RE NOT GONNA GO.

34:13.920 --> 34:15.748
WHAT, YOU'RE GONNA MISS
THE MAIDEN VOYAGE
AFTER ALL THAT WORK YOU PUT IN?

34:15.879 --> 34:17.793
-WELL, HOBIE HASN'T SEEN
SAN DIEGO, YOU KNOW,

34:17.925 --> 34:19.405
I WAS GONNA SHOW HIM AROUND.

34:19.534 --> 34:20.884
-I DON'T THINK THAT'S
SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

34:21.014 --> 34:22.886
-COME ON, DAD, PLEASE?

34:23.016 --> 34:24.931
-YEAH, GO ON, MITCH,
JUST LET THEM GO.

34:25.063 --> 34:26.411
USED TO DO THE SAME
THING TO MOM AND DAD.

34:27.326 --> 34:29.371
THEY DON'T WANNA HANG
WITH A COUPLE OF STIFFS.

34:29.502 --> 34:31.982
ALRIGHT, YOU GO ON, JUST MAKE
SURE YOU'RE BACK AT DARK.

34:32.112 --> 34:33.245
-DUDE, LET'S BAIL.

34:34.246 --> 34:35.943
-THANKS, DAD, BYE!

34:36.074 --> 34:36.944
-BYE, HOBE.

34:46.214 --> 34:49.522
[GENTLE MUSIC]

34:52.786 --> 34:53.656
-STEPHANIE: HI.

34:54.396 --> 34:55.397
-MATT: HI.

34:55.527 --> 34:56.790
SO HOW DID WE DO?

34:56.920 --> 34:58.400
-YOU WERE TERRIFIC,
THANKS, GUYS.

34:58.531 --> 35:00.315
-SO YOU THINK YOU'RE
GONNA GET YOUR NEW SCARAB?

35:00.446 --> 35:03.405
-NO ONE WAS GOING FOR THEIR
CHECKBOOK, BUT I'M OPTIMISTIC.

35:03.536 --> 35:05.015
-WELL, IF THERE'S
ANYTHING ELSE WE CAN DO.

35:05.146 --> 35:06.321
-NO, THAT'S IT, YOU GOT

35:06.452 --> 35:07.409
THE REST OF THE WEEKEND
TO YOURSELVES.

35:07.540 --> 35:08.367
ENJOY THE DEL.

35:08.497 --> 35:09.324
-WE WILL.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.631
-STEPHANIE: HEY,
WHERE YOU GOING?

35:11.761 --> 35:12.806
-WE'RE GOING SNORKELING.

35:12.936 --> 35:14.242
WE'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

35:14.373 --> 35:15.983
-SUMMER: BYE, MEL.
-STEPHANIE: BYE-BYE.

35:16.549 --> 35:18.028
I WONDER WHERE
MITCH AND HOBIE ARE.

35:18.638 --> 35:20.379
-THEY WENT SAILING
WITH HIS BROTHER.

35:20.509 --> 35:22.294
-OH, THAT'S RIGHT.

35:22.424 --> 35:24.470
AND I ASSUME THAT YOU'RE GONNA
BE GOING BACK TO SEA WORLD.

35:24.600 --> 35:26.036
-YOU WANNA COME?

35:26.167 --> 35:28.430
-[LAUGHING]
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

35:28.561 --> 35:30.171
I THINK I'LL JUST
HANG AROUND THE HOTEL.

35:30.302 --> 35:32.391
-OKAY, BYE.

35:32.521 --> 35:34.175
-MEL: SEE YA.
-OH, C.J.?

35:35.263 --> 35:38.919
HAS SUMMER SAID ANYTHING
MORE ABOUT THE INVISIBLE MAN?

35:39.049 --> 35:40.964
-NO, SHE'S BACK ON
PLANET EARTH NOW.

35:41.617 --> 35:42.531
-GOOD.

35:43.228 --> 35:45.012
-WHAT IS IT YOU WERE
SAYING ABOUT, SUMMER?

35:45.143 --> 35:47.710
-OH, YESTERDAY, SUMMER
WAS TELLING US ABOUT THIS

35:47.841 --> 35:51.323
MYSTERIOUS PRESENCE SHE WAS
FEELING AROUND THE HOTEL.

35:51.932 --> 35:55.240
I DON'T KNOW, I'M SURE
IT WAS ALL IN HER MIND.

35:55.370 --> 35:57.416
SUMMER CAN BE JUST
A LITTLE DRAMATIC SOMETIMES.

35:58.373 --> 35:59.244
-THAT'S INTERESTING.

36:00.593 --> 36:01.420
-WHAT'S INTERESTING?

36:02.029 --> 36:02.986
-MYSTERIOUS PRESENCE.

36:03.596 --> 36:06.207
LEGEND HAS IT THIS HOTEL
IS HAUNTED BY A GHOST.

36:06.947 --> 36:09.906
[EERIE MUSIC]

36:54.995 --> 36:57.954
-OH, STEPHANIE,
AM I GLAD TO SEE YOU.

36:58.085 --> 36:58.999
-WHAT'S WRONG, ARE YOU OKAY?

36:59.129 --> 37:00.696
-NO, I'M NOT OKAY.

37:00.827 --> 37:02.959
I REALLY JUST WANT TO LEAVE
THIS HOTEL AND GO HOME.

37:03.090 --> 37:04.483
-SUMMER, I WANNA
SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

37:04.613 --> 37:05.701
-WHAT?

37:05.832 --> 37:07.094
-THIS IS A BOOK
ABOUT THE HOTEL.

37:07.660 --> 37:09.227
SUPPOSEDLY, IT IS HAUNTED.

37:09.792 --> 37:10.793
-HAUNTED?

37:10.924 --> 37:12.708
LIKE, BY A GHOST?

37:12.839 --> 37:14.797
SEE, STEPHANIE,
I WASN'T HALLUCINATING,

37:14.928 --> 37:16.538
THERE REALLY IS A GHOST.

37:17.060 --> 37:18.758
-IT SAYS HERE THAT 50 YEARS AGO

37:18.888 --> 37:21.021
A MAN NAMED RUPERT
MANSFIELD FELL TO HIS DEATH

37:21.151 --> 37:23.284
FROM THE TOP
OF THE SOUTHWEST SPIRE,

37:23.415 --> 37:27.419
HE'D BEEN HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH A MARRIED SOCIALITE
NAMED DIANA SUTHERLAND.

37:28.071 --> 37:29.464
THE POLICE RULED IT A SUICIDE,

37:29.595 --> 37:30.813
BUT A LOT OF PEOPLE
THOUGHT IT WAS MURDER.

37:30.944 --> 37:33.381
NOBODY KNOWS WHAT
REALLY HAPPENED.

37:34.991 --> 37:39.431
OH, LOOK AT THIS, IT SAYS
HE WAS STAYING IN ROOM 318.

37:40.083 --> 37:41.911
-HMM, WHERE'S ROOM 318?

37:42.521 --> 37:45.959
-THERE IS NO 318,
THE ROOMS HAVE BEEN RENUMBERED.

37:46.916 --> 37:48.657
IT'S NOW ROOM 3018.

37:49.397 --> 37:52.270
-OH, MY GOD, STEPHANIE,
THAT'S MY ROOM.

37:54.402 --> 37:56.012
WHAT DO YOU THINK
HE WANTS WITH ME?

37:57.405 --> 37:58.885
-THIS IS DIANA SUTHERLAND.

38:07.589 --> 38:09.330
AND THERE'S RUPERT MANSFIELD.

38:20.341 --> 38:25.520
[GENTLE MUSIC]

38:32.527 --> 38:35.400
-HAHA, MAN, BEAUTIFUL
OUT HERE, BRO.

38:35.530 --> 38:36.575
-AWESOME.

38:37.184 --> 38:38.533
-WE COULD JUST KEEP GOING.

38:39.534 --> 38:41.754
GOT ENOUGH FOOD TO
MAKE IT TO HAWAII,
THE BOYS WOULD UNDERSTAND.

38:41.884 --> 38:42.929
-YOU KNOW YOU'RE UNREAL.

38:43.059 --> 38:45.627
-IT WAS A JOKE,
MAN, I WAS KIDDING.

38:45.758 --> 38:46.889
-NO, YOU WEREN'T.

38:47.977 --> 38:51.067
-MITCH, LOOK,
I'M SORRY ABOUT YESTERDAY.

38:51.677 --> 38:54.288
I HAD NO RIGHT TO
ASK YOU TO TAKE KYLE.

38:55.202 --> 38:57.770
I NEVER SHOULD'VE BROUGHT IT UP,
I WAS WAY OUT OF LINE,
I APOLOGIZE.

38:58.553 --> 39:01.774
BUT I... I FIGURED IF I KNEW
HE WAS IN GOOD HANDS

39:01.904 --> 39:03.689
I WOULDN'T FEEL SO
DAMN GUILTY, THAT'S ALL.

39:06.692 --> 39:08.520
-I'LL TAKE HIM.
-WHAT?

39:08.650 --> 39:09.782
-I SAID I'LL TAKE HIM.

39:11.479 --> 39:13.176
KYLE CAN COME AND LIVE
WITH ME AND HOBIE.

39:13.307 --> 39:15.135
-YOU MEAN THAT FOR REAL?

39:15.265 --> 39:17.093
-WHY NOT? I'VE BEEN BAILING
YOU OUT YOUR ENTIRE LIFE,

39:17.224 --> 39:18.138
WHY STOP NOW?

39:18.268 --> 39:19.966
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

39:20.096 --> 39:21.794
I LOVE YOU, BRO.

39:25.885 --> 39:27.800
-WIND'S PICKING UP,
WE BETTER JIBE.

39:27.930 --> 39:29.454
-HEY, STAND BY THE JIBE.

39:29.584 --> 39:30.411
COME ON, TAKE OVER.

39:37.113 --> 39:38.941
[GRUNTING]

39:43.468 --> 39:44.860
-BUZZY!

39:46.079 --> 39:49.082
BUZZY, YOU ALRIGHT?
-I'M OKAY, MAN,
IT JUST GRAZED ME.

39:49.212 --> 39:50.213
-HANG ON.

39:50.344 --> 39:52.041
-HURRY UP.

39:52.172 --> 39:53.956
-LET ME UNTIE THIS LOOP.

39:59.005 --> 40:00.006
GRAB THE BUOY!

40:06.491 --> 40:07.796
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

40:08.841 --> 40:10.582
-I DON'T KNOW, IT'S MY CHEST.

40:10.712 --> 40:12.148
I CAN'T BREATHE.

40:12.279 --> 40:13.323
